%N A396540 a(1) = 1; for n > 1, a(n) is the smallest number > 5^(n-1) with exactly n divisors.
%F A396540 a(p) = 7^(p-1) for p prime. - _Daniel Suteu_, Jun 09 2026
%e A396540 a(2) = 7 because it is the smallest number > 5^(2-1) with exactly 2 divisors;
%e A396540 a(3) = 49 because it is the smallest number > 5^(3-1) with exactly 3 divisors;
%e A396540 a(4) = 129 because it is the smallest number > 5^(4-1) with exactly 4 divisors.
%o A396540 (Magma) [1] cat [Min([k: k in [5^(n-1)+1..7^(n-1)] | #Divisors(k) eq n]): n in [2..9]];
%o A396540 (PARI) a(n) = if(n<=1, return(1)); if(isprime(n), return(7^(n-1))); for(k=5^(n-1)+1, oo, if(numdiv(k) == n, return(k))); \\ _Daniel Suteu_, Jun 09 2026
